etymologies: Middle English; earliest use found in The Childhood of Jesus. From early Scandinavian (compare Old Icelandic títt frequently, often, Old Swedish tit often, quickly (Swedish regional tidt quickly), Norwegian (Nynorsk) tidt often, Danish tidt (Danish tit often)), use as adverb of the neuter singular of the adjective represented by Old Icelandic tíðr frequent, customary
